Program: Outlook
Title: 21/11/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00ljjqn
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 22 Nov 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Jesmyn Ward, the American woman who turned her terrifying experience of Hurricane Katrina into an award-winning novel. Salvage the Bones by Jesmyn Ward is published by Bloomsbury. Also, we go on the beat with one of Afghanistan's new breed of women police officers. And a British journalist describes the madness he experienced when a routine hospital operation went wrong. Show less